# TPBench CPU kernel registry
#
# Format: NAME|TAGS|PATH
#   NAME  - kernel name (must match tpbk_<NAME>.c)
#   TAGS  - comma-separated tags for build selection
#   PATH  - directory relative to this file containing tpbk_<NAME>.c
#
# Edit this file to add kernels in nested directories.

stream|default,bandwidth|simple
triad|default,bandwidth|simple
scale|default,bandwidth|simple
axpy|default,bandwidth|simple
rtriad|default,bandwidth|simple
sum|default,bandwidth|simple
staxpy|bandwidth,stanza|simple
striad|bandwidth,stanza|simple
stream_mpi|bandwidth,mpi|streaming_memory_access_mpi
